      "writtenOn": "2021-04-09T19:04:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hm, this is tricky; if someone does actually look and fix configs quickly, then this is OK, but otherwise it would cause logs to bounce around inside of logdog\u0027s state for a while.\n\nI think I\u0027d prefer to loudly log the error along with the project name so that we can then fix the configs; I don\u0027t think clients should expect us to keep their data with invalid configuration?",
      "parentUuid": "b7cb0315_a651d543",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 233,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 234,
        "endChar": 51
      },
      "revId": "d559af7863599f687628a5a7875187794f934099",
